ds|type=album|artist=Bebe Rexha|title=Expectations|award=Gold|relyear=2018|certyear=2019|accessdate=July 26, 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|type=album|artist=Bebe Rexha|title=Expectations|award=Gold|relyear=2018|certyear=2018|salesamount=604,000<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hitsdailydouble.com/news&id=314588&title=2018-TOP-50-ALBUMS&redirect=mobile|title=HITS Daily Double : Rumor Mill - 2018 TOP 50 ALBUMS|website=HITS Daily Double|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|streaming=true|nosales=true}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Bebe Rexha}}\n[[Category:2018 debut albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Hit-Boy]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Jason Evigan]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Joey Moi]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Louis Bell]]\n[[Category:Bebe Rexha albums]]\n[[Category:Warner Records albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 studio album by Bebe Rexha}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Expectations\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Bebe Rexha]]\n| cover      = Expectations-Bebe-Rexha.png\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2018|6|22}}\n| recorded   = 2016\u20132018\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Pop music|Pop]]<ref name=AllMusic/>|[[electropop]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8462622/bebe-rexha-expectations-album-lyrics-intoxicating-meanings|title=Bebe Rexha's 6 Most Intoxicating Lyrics From New 'Expectations' Album|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|first=Heran|last=Mamo|date=June 25, 2018|accessdate=September 14, 2019}}</ref>}}\n| length     = {{duration|m=43|s=47}}\n| label      = [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]]\n| producer   =\n* [[Louis Bell]]\n* Devon Corey\n* [[Captain Cuts]]\n* [[Jason Evigan]]\n* [[David Garcia (musician)|David Garcia]]\n* German\n* [[Hit-Boy]]\n* Jussifer \n* [[Joey Moi]]\n* [[The Monsters and the Strangerz]]\n* Ali P\n* Dre Pinckney\n* Robot Scott\n* [[The Stereotypes]]\n* Gian Stone\n* Andrew Wells\n* Willshire\n* Aaron Zuckerman\n| prev_title = [[All Your Fault: Pt. 2]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{Singles\n<!-- \"I Got You\" and \"Meant to Be\" are singles from the All Your Fault series. They do not promote this album and addition of these songs as singles will be reverted. -->\n | name        = Expectations\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[I'm a Mess (Bebe Rexha song)|I'm a Mess]]\n | single1date = June 15, 2018\n }}\n}}\n\n'''''Expectations''''' is the debut studio album by American singer [[Bebe Rexha]]. It was released on June 22, 2018, by [[Warner Bros. Records]]. The album was announced following the success of her collaboration with country duo [[Florida Georgia Line]], \"[[Meant to Be (Bebe Rexha song)|Meant to Be]]\". ''Expectations'' went out for pre-order on April 13, 2018, with the release of two promotional singles: \"Ferrari\" and \"2 Souls on Fire\".<ref name=\"itunes\">{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/expectations/1370924192 |title=Expectations by Bebe Rexha |work=[[iTunes Store]] (US) |accessdate=April 14, 2018}}</ref> The album includes the singles \"[[I Got You (Bebe Rexha song)|I Got You]]\" and \"[[Meant to Be (Bebe Rexha song)|Meant to Be]]\" from ''[[All Your Fault: Pt. 1]]'' and ''[[All Your Fault: Pt. 2]]'', respectively. It features appearances from rappers [[Quavo]] and [[Tory Lanez]], and country music duo Florida Georgia Line. The album sold 604,000 units in the U.S. as of January 29, 2019 (37,000 pure).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://hitsdailydouble.com/news&id=314588&title=2018-TOP-50-ALBUMS&redirect=mobile|title=HITS Daily Double : Rumor Mill - 2018 TOP 50 ALBUMS|website=HITS Daily Double|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nFollowing the release of ''[[All Your Fault: Pt. 2]]'', Bebe began teasing new songs for a third installment in the ''All Your Fault'' series, with her manager going on record about its release.<ref name=\"ayfpt3\">{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/7964606/bebe-rexha-template-artist-development-age-streaming |title=Bebe Rexha's Template For Artist Development In the Age of Streaming |work=Billboard |author=Andy Gensler |date=September 12, 2017 |accessdate=April 14, 2018}}</ref> However, it appeared plans had changed, as Rexha revealed her next project would be called ''Expectations'' through a tweet in November 2017.<ref name=\"exconf\">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/BebeRexha/status/928684814470803456 |title=Bebe Rexha on Twitter: \"Current Updates: New project coming in New year #Expectations. New record with Machine Gun X Ambassadors called \"Home\" coming soon.\" |author=Bebe Rexha |via=Twitter |accessdate=April 14, 2018}}</ref> Rexha revealed the cover art on April 8, 2018, with the album being available for pre-order on April 13.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.idolator.com/7677107/bebe-rexha-expectations-debut-album-cover|title=Bebe Rexha Reveals The Cover Of Debut LP, 'Expectations'|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=April 9, 2018|accessdate=April 15, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"album announcement\">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/BebeRexha/status/982983402600017920 |title=Bebe Rexha on Twitter: \"My Debut album \"Expectations\" our for pre-order this Friday April 13th.\" |author=Bebe Rexha |via=Twitter |accessdate=April 14, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Singles==\n\"[[I'm a Mess (Bebe Rexha song)|I'm a Mess]]\" was released as the first single exclusive to the album on June 15, following an early radio release in the United States.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://twitter.com/BebeRexha/status/1005260603596865537|title=Bebe Rexha on Twitter: \"We sent all the radio stations a version so they can live with it & hopefully like it enough to play it. Some stations loved it & played it\"|date=June 8, 2018|accessdate=June 10, 2018}}</ref> It has so far peaked at number 35 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], becoming Rexha's first top 40 hit as a solo lead artist. \"[[I Got You (Bebe Rexha song)|I Got You]]\" and \"[[Meant to Be (Bebe Rexha song)|Meant to Be]]\" featuring [[Florida Georgia Line]], from the first and second parts of ''All Your Fault'' respectively, were also included on the album. \n\n===Promotional singles===\n\"Ferrari\" and \"2 Souls on Fire\", the latter of which features [[Quavo]] of [[Migos]], were released as promotional singles on April 13, 2018 with the pre-order of the album. \"Ferrari\" has since received a vertical video.<ref>{{Citation|last=Bebe Rexha|title=Bebe Rexha - Ferrari [Vertical Video]|date=2018-04-27|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nyRawESIuy4|access-date=2018-09-16}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n<!-- DO NOT add more than 10 reviews per [[Template:Album ratings]]. -->\n| MC = 65/100<ref name=\"Metacriticrv\">{{cite web|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/expectations/bebe-rexha/critic-reviews |title=Critic Reviews for Expectations|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=June 25, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{rating|3|5}}<ref name=AllMusic>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/expectations-mw0003170835 |title=Expectations \u2013 Bebe Rexha |website=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=June 23, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev2score = {{rating|1|5}}<ref name=Guardian>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2018/jun/22/bebe-rexha-expectations-review-fiercely-trite-pop |title=Bebe Rexha: Expectations review \u2013 fiercely trite pop |work=[[The Guardian]] |location=London |date=June 22, 2018 |accessdate=June 23, 2018 |last=Snapes |first=Laura}}</ref>\n| rev3 = [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]\n| rev3score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=Idolator>{{cite news|url=http://www.idolator.com/7681872/album-review-bebe-rexha-expectations |title=Album Review: Bebe Rexha's 'Expectations' |work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |date=June 22, 2018 |accessdate=June 23, 2018 |last=Nied |first=Mike}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[The Independent]]''\n| rev4score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"Independent\">{{cite news| url = https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/5sos-new-album-review-bebe-rexha-nine-inch-nails-kamasi-washington-a8408281.html| title = Album reviews: 5SOS, Bebe Rexha, Nine Inch Nails and more\n| work=[[The Independent]] |date=June 20, 2018|accessdate=June 23, 2018| first1=Ilana | last1=Kaplan | first2=Nick | last2=Hasted}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[NME]]''\n| rev5score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref name=\"NME\">{{cite news|url=http://www.nme.com/reviews/album/bebe-rexha-expectations-review |title=Expectations \u2013 Bebe Rexha review |work=[[NME]] |date=June 22, 2018 |accessdate=June 23, 2018 |last=Levine |first=Nick}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev6Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/review-bebe-rexhas-expectations-w522134|title=Bebe Rexha's 'Expectations' Revels In Nineties-Loving Loneliness|last=Grant|first=Sarah|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=June 27, 2018|accessdate=June 27, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[The Quietus]]''\n| rev7Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=\"The Quietus\">{{cite web|url=http://thequietus.com/articles/24900-bebe-rexha-expectations-album-review|title=Bebe Rexha - Expectations Review|last=Monroe|first=Tommy|work=[[The Quietus]]|date=July 2, 2018|accessdate=July 3, 2018}}</ref>\n<!-- DO NOT add more than 10 reviews per [[Template:Album ratings]]. -->\n}} \n\nAccording to [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[weighted mean]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, the album received an [[weighted arithmetic mean|average]] score of 65, based on six reviews, indicating \u201cgenerally favorable reviews\u201d<ref name=\"Metacriticrv\"/>. [[AllMusic]]'s Neil Z. Yeung viewed the album as \"an improvement upon her trio of EP releases that succeeds in presenting mature, forward-thinking pop of the dark, introspective variety\" and concluded, \"While it could benefit from some tightening \u2013 the middle stretch stalls the momentum \u2013 ''Expectations'' affirms Rexha's songwriting prowess, ear for catchy hooks, and ability to pull emotion from otherwise serviceable radio pop\".<ref name=AllMusic/> Craig Jenkins from ''[[Vulture (blog)|Vulture]]'' referred to the album as \"a showcase for the versatility of her instrument, which is both high and hearty and also a little wan, capable of hitting incredible marks in its upper register at the cost of coming in a little shrill\". He especially praised album's intriguing ideas, playful lyrics and memorable hooks, dubbing it \"one of the week's easiest pleasures\".<ref name=Vulture>{{cite journal|url=http://www.vulture.com/2018/06/review-bebe-rexhas-album-expectations.html |title=Bebe Rexha's Expectations Explores Weird, Bad Feelings |work=[[Vulture (blog)|Vulture]] |date=June 22, 2018 |accessdate=June 24, 2018 |last=Jenkins |first=Craig}}</ref>\n\nIlana Kaplan and Nick Hasted from ''[[The Independent]]'' highlighted album's ballads \"Grace\" and \"Knees\", describing ''Expectations'' as \"album full of flawed, self-deprecating and boundary-pushing pop offerings\".<ref name=\"Independent\"/> [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]'s Mike Nied stated that the album \"perfectly captures the superstar's ethos\" and that Rexha's \"very recognizable voice is absolutely riveting.\" Nevertheless, he opined that the inclusion of \"[[Meant to Be (Bebe Rexha song)|Meant to Be]]\" \"feels out of place\", despite being \"her biggest hit to date\".<ref name=Idolator/> Nick Levine from ''[[NME]]'' perceived Rexha more as an \"emo singer\",<ref name=\"NME\"/> while ''[[Refinery29]]''{{'}}s Courtney E. Smith described Rexha as an \"anti-hero\" and a \"dangerous woman fiercely playing with themes of depression, a lack of self-control, and unpredictability\". In addition, Smith expressed that the singer \"did a masterful job of painting a nihilistic scene in which she's an observer, and sometimes an unreliable narrator\", but emphasized a lack of \"autobiographical impression\".<ref name=\"Refinery29\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.refinery29.com/2018/06/202511/bebe-rexha-expectations-album-review |title=Bebe Rexha Isn't Afraid To Be An Anti-Hero With Expectations |work=[[Refinery29]] |date=June 22, 2018 |accessdate=June 24, 2018 |last=E. Smith |first=Courtney}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]''{{'}}s Sarah Grant wrote that on ''Expectations'', Rexha \"paints herself as a heroine trapped in an ivory tower of her own making, but her cat-scratching upper register suggests sensitivity more than vengeance\", calling it \"an impressive debut album full of nostalgic heartache\".<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\"/> Tommy Monroe from ''[[The Quietus]]'' stated that \"a few tracks do do lack energy\", however he described Rexha as \"no ordinary singer\" and \"a chameleon who can switch vocals, blend with any sound, and find rhythm with any tempo\".<ref name=\"The Quietus\"/>\n\nIn a less positive review, Laura Snapes of ''[[The Guardian]]'' criticized the overuse of [[Auto-Tune]] and Rexha's \"desperate search of an identity\" throughout the album, citing \"Ferrari\" as the \"only remotely distinctive song\".<ref name=Guardian/>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Standard edition<ref name=\"itunes\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/90295251|title=Bebe Rexha - Expectations|website=listen.tidal.com|accessdate=June 21, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media notes|title=Expectations|others=[[Bebe Rexha]]|year=2018|publisher=[[Warner Bros. Records]]}}</ref>\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| total_length = 43:47\n| title1 = Ferrari\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Bebe Rexha|Bleta Rexha]]|[[Jason Evigan]]|Asia Whiteacre}}\n| extra1 = {{hlist|Evigan|Gian Stone{{ref|a|[a]}}}}\n| length1 = 3:32\n| title2 = [[I'm a Mess (Bebe Rexha song)|I'm a Mess]]\n| writer2 = {{hlist|Rexha|Jussi Karvinen|[[Justin Tranter]]|[[Meredith Brooks]]|[