 on what reliable sources list them as and not on personal interpretations. Limit of the three most relevant genres in accordance with [[MOS:A&M]]. -->\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Print\n| type            = manga\n| author          = Taku Kuwabara\n| publisher       = [[Kodansha]]\n| publisher_en    = {{English manga publisher|NA=[[Kodansha USA]]}}\n| demographic     = ''[[Seinen manga|Seinen]]''\n| magazine        = [[good! Afternoon]]\n| first           = June 7, 2016\n| last            = \n| volumes         = 8\n| volume_list     = #volume list\n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Video\n| type            = TV series \n| director        = Tadahiro Yoshihira\n| writer          = [[Makoto Uezu]]\n| music           = [[Masaru Yokoyama]]\n| studio          = [[Polygon Pictures]]\n| licensee        = [[Netflix]]\n| network         = [[Fuji TV]] ([[+Ultra]]), [[Kansai Telecasting Corporation|KTV]], [[T\u014dkai Television Broadcasting|THK]], [[Television Nishinippon Corporation|TNC]], [[Hokkaido Cultural Broadcasting|UHB]], [[Fuji Network System|BS Fuji]]\n| first           = January 9, 2020\n| last            = March 26, 2020\n| episodes        = 12\n| episode_list    = \n}}\n{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}\n{{Nihongo|'''''Drifting Dragons'''''|\u7a7a\u633a\u30c9\u30e9\u30b4\u30f3\u30ba|K\u016btei Doragonzu|{{trans}} \"Airborne Dragons\"}} is a Japanese [[manga]] series written and illustrated by Taku Kuwabara. It has been serialized in [[Kodansha]]'s [[seinen manga|''seinen'' manga]] magazine ''[[good! Afternoon]]'' since June 2016 and has been collected in eight ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volumes as of March 2020. The manga is published digitally in English by [[Kodansha USA]] under the Kodansha Comics imprint.\n\nAn [[anime]] television series adaptation by [[Polygon Pictures]] premiered on January 9, 2020 on [[Fuji TV]]'s [[+Ultra]] programming block, to be followed by an international [[Netflix]] release on April 30, 2020.<ref name=\"Netflix\">{{cite web|url=https://animeuknews.net/2020/01/the-list-of-new-anime-shows-films-coming-to-netflix-in-2020-beyond/|title=The List of New Anime Shows & Films Coming to Netflix in 2020 & Beyond|website=Anime UK News|access-date=January 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://popculture.com/streaming/2020/03/19/netflix-april-2020-everything-coming-leaving/|title=Everything Coming to Netflix in April 2020|website=Pop Culture|access-date=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Characters==\n;{{Nihongo|Mika|\u30df\u30ab|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Tomoaki Maeno]]}}<ref name=\"cast\" />\n;{{Nihongo|Takita|\u30bf\u30ad\u30bf|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Sora Amamiya]]}}<ref name=\"cast\">{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-10-09/drifting-dragons-tv-anime-reveals-teaser-video-18-cast-members/.152048 |title=Drifting Dragons TV Anime Reveals Teaser Video, 18 Cast Members |date=October 9, 2019|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=October 9, 2019}}</ref>\n;{{Nihongo|Jiro|\u30b8\u30ed\u30fc|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[S\u014dma Sait\u014d]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Vanabelle|\u30f4\u30a1\u30ca\u30d9\u30eb|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Kana Hanazawa]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Gibbs|\u30ae\u30d6\u30b9|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Junichi Suwabe]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Crocco|\u30af\u30ed\u30c3\u30b3|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Tomokazu Seki]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Niko|\u30cb\u30b3|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Takahiro Sakurai]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Berko|\u30d0\u30fc\u30b3|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[K\u014dsuke Toriumi]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Capella|\u30ab\u30da\u30e9|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Rie Kugimiya]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Gaga|\u30ac\u30ac|}}\n:{{Voiced by|Kentar\u014d Kumagai}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Faye|\u30d5\u30a7\u30a4|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Makoto Furukawa]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Badakin|\u30d0\u30c0\u30ad\u30f3|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Takashi Matsuyama (actor)|Takashi Matsuyama]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Oken|\u30aa\u30fc\u30b1\u30f3|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Shunsuke Takeuchi]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Soroya|\u30bd\u30e9\u30e4|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Y\u016bto Uemura]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Mayne|\u30e1\u30a4\u30f3|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Chinatsu Akasaki]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Hiro|\u30d2\u30fc\u30ed|}}\n:{{Voiced by|Junya Enoki}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Yoshi|\u30e8\u30b7|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Kazuhiko Inoue]]}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Lee|\u30ea\u30fc|}}\n:{{Voiced by|Hiroo Sasaki}}<ref name=\"cast\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Katja|\u30ab\u30fc\u30c1\u30e3|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Ayane Sakura]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\">{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2020-01-06/drifting-dragons-tv-anime-casts-ayane-sakura-sayaka-senbongi-maaya-sakamoto-kiyonobu-suzuki/.155085|title=Drifting Dragons TV Anime Casts Ayane Sakura, Sayaka Senbongi, Maaya Sakamoto, Kiyonobu Suzuki |date=January 6, 2020|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=January 6, 2020}}</ref>\n;{{Nihongo|Nanami|\u30ca\u30ca\u30df|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Sayaka Senbongi]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Ascella|\u30a2\u30b9\u30b1\u30e9|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Maaya Sakamoto]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n;{{Nihongo|Ura|\u30a6\u30e9\u723a|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Kiyonobu Suzuki]]}}<ref name=\"cast2\"/>\n\n==Media==\n===Manga===\n''Drifting Dragons'' is written and illustrated by Taku Kuwabara. It started its publication in [[Kodansha]]'s ''[[good! Afternoon]]'' on June 7, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u9f8d\u98df\u3044\u3066\u3048\uff01\u300c\u3068\u3063\u304b\u3076\u300d\u306e\u6851\u539f\u592a\u77e9\u3001\u65b0\u4f5c\u306f\u7a7a\u98db\u3076\u6355\u9f8d\u8239\u63cf\u304f\u30b0\u30eb\u30e1\u7d00\u884c |url=https://natalie.mu/comic/news/189964 |website=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] |accessdate=April 11, 2020 |language=ja |date=June 7, 2016}}</ref> Kodansha has published the series into individual ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volumes. The first volume was released on November 7, 2016.<ref name=\"vol1jp\"/> As of March 2020, eight ''tank\u014dbon'' volumes have been released.<ref name=\"vol8jp\"/>\n\nIn North America, [[Kodansha USA]] announced the digital release of the manga in November 2017.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hodgkins |first1=Crystalyn |title=Kodansha USA Reveals 6 More Digital Manga Licenses |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-11-18/kodansha-usa-reveals-6-more-digital-manga-licenses/.124224 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=April 11, 2020 |date=November 18, 2017}}</ref> They also announced the print release of the manga in March 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sherman |first1=Jennifer |title=Kodansha Comics, Vertical Add Bakemonogatari, Cells at Work! Code Black, Granblue Fantasy Manga |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-03-13/kodansha-comics-vertical-add-bakemonogatari-cells-at-work-code-black-granblue-fantasy-manga/.144500 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=April 11, 2020 |date=March 13, 2019}}</ref> The first volume was published on December 17, 2019.<ref name=\"vol1en\"/>\n\n====Volume list====\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n | Language        = Japanese\n | Width        = 100%\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 1\n| OriginalRelDate = November 7, 2016<ref name=\"vol1jp\">{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u7a7a\u633a\u30c9\u30e9\u30b4\u30f3\u30ba\uff08\uff11\uff09 |url=http://kc.kodansha.co.jp/product?item=0000047558|publisher=[[Kodansha]] |accessdate=April 11, 2020 |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n| OriginalISBN    = 978-4-06-388204-9\n| LicensedRelDate = December 17, 2019<ref name=\"vol1en\">{{cite web |title=Drifting Dragons, Volume 1 |url=https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/616746/drifting-dragons-1-by-taku-kuwabara/ |publisher=[[Penguin Random House]] |accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| LicensedISBN  = 9781632368904\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 2\n| OriginalRelDate = May 1, 2017<ref>{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u7a7a\u633a\u30c9\u30e9\u30b4\u30f3\u30ba\uff08\uff12\uff09 |url=http://kc.kodansha.co.jp/product?item=0000047609|publisher=[[Kodansha]] 