.com/books/645770/drifting-dragons-7-by-taku-kuwabara/ |publisher=[[Penguin Random House]] |accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| LicensedISBN  = 9781646510368\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 8\n| OriginalRelDate = March 6, 2020<ref name=\"vol8jp\">{{cite web |script-title=ja:\u7a7a\u633a\u30c9\u30e9\u30b4\u30f3\u30ba\uff08\uff18\uff09 |url=http://kc.kodansha.co.jp/product?item=0000338548|publisher=[[Kodansha]] |accessdate=April 11, 2020 |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n| OriginalISBN    = 978-4-06-518878-1\n| LicensedRelDate = \u2013\n| LicensedISBN  = \n}}\n{{Graphic novel list/footer}}\n\n===Anime===\nAn [[anime]] television series adaptation was announced on March 15, 2019. The series is animated by [[Polygon Pictures]] and directed by Tadahiro Yoshihira, with [[Makoto Uezu]] handling series composition, Kyoko Kotani designing the characters, and [[Masaru Yokoyama]] composing the music.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://drifting-dragons.jp/staffcast/staff.php|title=Staff&Cast|accessdate=October 10, 2019|language=Japanese}}</ref> It premiered on January 9, 2020 on [[Fuji TV]]'s [[+Ultra]] programming block, as well as [[Kansai Telecasting Corporation|KTV]], [[T\u014dkai Television Broadcasting|THK]], [[Television Nishinippon Corporation|TNC]], [[Hokkaido Cultural Broadcasting|UHB]], and [[Fuji Network System|BS Fuji]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-29/drifting-dragons-tv-anime-reveals-video-january-8-premiere/.153826|title=Drifting Dragons TV Anime Reveals Video, January 8 Premiere|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 29, 2019|accessdate=November 29, 2019}}</ref> The series will also stream on [[Netflix]].<ref name=\"Netflix\"/> Yoh Kamiyama performed the series' opening theme song \"Gunj\u014d\", while Akai Ko-en performed the series' ending theme song \"Zettai Reido\".<ref name=\"cast\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-12-25/drifting-dragons-tv-anime-video-reveals-yoh-kamiyama-opening-song/.154752|title=Drifting Dragons TV Anime Video Reveals Yoh Kamiyama Opening Song|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 25, 2019|accessdate=December 25, 2019}}</ref> It ran for 12 episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2020-01-10/drifting-dragons-anime-has-12-episodes/.155225|title=Drifting Dragons Anime Has 12 Episodes|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=January 10, 2020|accessdate=January 10, 2020}}</ref><!--\n\n====Episode list====\n{|class=\"plainrowheaders wikitable\" style=\"width:98%; margin:auto; background:#FFF;\n|- style=\"border-bottom: 3px solid #CCF;\"\n! style=\"width:4em;\"  | {{Abbr|No.|Number}}\n! Title\n! style=\"width:12em;\" | Original air date\n|-\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 1\n| Title               = \n| TranslitTitle       = \n| NativeTitle         = \n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|1|9}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 2\n| Title               = \n| TranslitTitle       = \n| NativeTitle         = \n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|1|16}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 3\n| Title               = \n| TranslitTitle       = \n| NativeTitle         = \n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|1|23}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 4\n| Title               = \n| TranslitTitle       = \n| NativeTitle         = \n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|1|30}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 5\n| Title               = \n| TranslitTitle       = \n| NativeTitle         = \n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja\n| OriginalAirDate     = {{Start date|2020|2|6}}\n| ShortSummary        = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber       = 6\n| Title               = \n| TranslitTitle       = \n| NativeTitle         = \n| Nativ